#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_description.xml:8
#, no-c-format
msgid "Description of pre-built images"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: date
#: deployment_images_description.xml:16
#, no-c-format
msgid "2023-01-25"
msgstr "2023-01-25"

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:23
#, no-c-format
msgid "&slema; can be deployed using pre-built images. Currently, there are two types of images available: raw disk images and selfinstall ISOs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:27
#, no-c-format
msgid "&slema; raw images are delivered for the &x86-64; architecture, &zseries; ZSeries and also &aarch64;. The selfinstall images are currently delivered only for the &x86-64; architecture. The pre-built images are intended to be configured on the first boot by using either Ignition or Combustion. The boot loader detects the first boot; for more information see <xref linkend=\"sec-first-boot\"/> . Each image has default mounted subvolumes as described in <xref linkend=\"sec-default-partitioning\"/> . The procedure of deploying these images is described in <xref linkend=\"cha-images-procedure\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_description.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "Do not use firewall along with Podman"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:39
#, no-c-format
msgid "Using firewall along with Podman may result in missing Podman-related firewall rules after reloading the <literal>firewalld</literal> service. Therefore, it is recommended to keep the firewall disabled if you intend to use Podman."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_description.xml:46
#, no-c-format
msgid "&slema; as a &vmhost;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "&slema; can run as a &kvm; host server&mdash;&xen; is not supported. However, there are several limitations of &slema; running as a &vmhost;; for details refer to <link xlink:href=\"https://documentation.suse.com/sles/15-SP3/html/SLES-all/cha-virt-support.html\">virtualization limits and support</link> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_description.xml:56
#, no-c-format
msgid "Default partitioning"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:58
#, no-c-format
msgid "The pre-built images are delivered with a default partitioning scheme, which can be changed during the first boot by using Ignition or Combustion. For a procedure to repartition the system, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-ignition-configuration\"/> or <xref linkend=\"sec-combustion-script\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_description.xml:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "Btrfs is mandatory for the root file system"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:68
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you intend to perform any changes to the default partitioning scheme, the root file system must be btrfs."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:74
#, no-c-format
msgid "Each image has the following subvolumes:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: deployment_images_description.xml:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"\n"
" /home\n"
" /root\n"
" /opt\n"
" /srv \n"
" /usr/local\n"
" /var\n"
" "
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "The images also have mounted subvolumes for booting by default. The specific subvolumes differ according to the architecture."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:92
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <literal>/etc</literal> directory is mounted as OverlayFS, where the upper directory is mounted to <filename>/var/lib/overlay/1/etc/</filename> . For details, refer to <xref linkend=\"sec-etc-overlay\"/> ."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:97
#, no-c-format
msgid "You can recognize the subvolumes mounted by default by the option <literal>x-initrd.mount</literal> in <filename>/etc/fstab</filename> . Other subvolumes or partitions must be configured either by Ignition or Combustion."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_description.xml:105
#, no-c-format
msgid "First boot detection"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:107
#, no-c-format
msgid "The configuration runs on the first boot only. To distinguish between the first and subsequent boots, the flag file <filename>/boot/writable/firstboot_happened</filename> is created after the first boot took place. If the file is not present in the file system, the attribute <literal>ignition.firstboot</literal> is passed to the kernel command line, and thus both Ignition and Combustion are triggered to run (in the <filename>initramfs</filename> ). After completing the first boot, the <filename>/boot/writable/firstboot_happened</filename> flag file is created."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: deployment_images_description.xml:120
#, no-c-format
msgid "The flag file is always created"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:121
#, no-c-format
msgid "Even though the configuration may not be successful, due to improper or missing configuration files, the <filename>/boot/writable/firstboot_happened</filename> flag file is created."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: deployment_images_description.xml:128
#, no-c-format
msgid "You may force the first boot configuration on subsequent boot by passing the <literal>ignition.firstboot</literal> attribute to the kernel command line or by deleting the <filename>/boot/writable/firstboot_happened</filename> flag file."
msgstr ""

